OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1784728097
OL,3,CRare puffling sighting offers hope for
OL,4,CDorset's dwindling puffin colony
OL,6,FThe monitoring project is being led by
OL,7,FDr Richard Caldow, an expert in
OL,8,Fseabird ecology, and supported by
OL,9,Fvolunteers from the Purbeck Natural
OL,10,FHistory Forum.
OL,12,F"With only three breeding pairs
OL,13,Fremaining, every chick matters," Dr
OL,14,FCaldow said.
OL,16,F"One puffling alone won't save this
OL,17,Fcolony, but one is a whole lot better
OL,18,Fnews than none.
OL,26,@tD@AOUuD@`O]xD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,389,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F388A1784728097
OL,3,CRare puffling sighting offers hope for
OL,4,CDorset's dwindling puffin colony
OL,6,F"We first observed fish being taken
OL,7,Finto the ledge on May 31, with the
OL,8,Flast fish delivery recorded on July 5.
OL,10,F"Based on this, we estimated the
OL,11,Fpuffling to be 38 to 40 days old.
OL,13,F"Puffins typically fledge between 38
OL,14,Fand 44 days after hatching, so it had
OL,15,Freached the minimum age at which it
OL,16,Fcould leave the nest."
OL,18,FThe puffling is expected to leave the
OL,19,Fledge and its parents under the cover
OL,20,Fof darkness and spend the next several
OL,21,Fyears alone at sea.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUuD@AOUxD@VO]
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
